# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SPEC-DRIFT SYNCHRONIZATION RULES
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Critical Sync Points

1. **Taxonomy Node Structure**
   - Spec Chapter 5 ↔ `taxonomy.schema.json` ↔ `simula_taxonomy_builder.py`
   - Changes to node fields must sync all three

2. **Dataset Specification Format**
   - Spec Chapter 7 ↔ `dataset-spec.schema.json`
   - Field additions require both spec and schema update

3. **Quality Thresholds**
   - Spec Chapter 10 ↔ Code constants in `simula_data_generator.py`
   - Threshold changes must be documented in spec

4. **Risk Categories**
   - Spec Appendix A1 ↔ `risk-register.yaml`
   - New risks must be documented in both places

## Pre-Change Checklist

Before modifying this specification:

- [ ] Run `make audit-spec-drift-domain DOMAIN=simula`
- [ ] Review `docs/schema/spec-code-mapping.yaml` for related artifacts
- [ ] Check implementation code for affected functions
- [ ] Verify test fixtures will remain valid

## Post-Change Checklist

After modifying this specification:

- [ ] Update `docs/schema/simula/*.schema.json` if data model changed
- [ ] Update `src/training/pipeline/` code if behavior changed
- [ ] Run `make audit-spec-drift` to verify synchronization
- [ ] Update `docs/summaries/simula-training-summary.md`

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CHAPTER STANDARDS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Required Chapter Elements

Each chapter MUST include:

1. **Chapter number and title** - Consistent numbering (01, 02, etc.)
2. **Section labels** - `\label{sec:simula-<topic>}` for cross-references
3. **Schema references** - Inline references to JSON schemas
4. **Code references** - References to implementation modules

## Citation Format

When referencing implementation details:

```latex
\textbf{Schema Reference:} \texttt{docs/schema/simula/taxonomy.schema.json}

\textbf{Implementation:} \texttt{src/training/pipeline/simula\_taxonomy\_builder.py}
```

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# REQUIREMENT ID CONVENTIONS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

| Category | Prefix | Example |
|----------|--------|---------|
| Data Generation | SIM-DG | SIM-DG-001 |
| Taxonomy | SIM-TAX | SIM-TAX-001 |
| Quality | SIM-QA | SIM-QA-001 |
| Lineage | SIM-LIN | SIM-LIN-001 |
| Infrastructure | SIM-INF | SIM-INF-001 |

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# QUALITY THRESHOLDS (Authoritative Values)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

These thresholds are authoritative - code MUST match:

| Metric | Value | Source |
|--------|-------|--------|
| Min taxonomy depth | 3 levels | Chapter 5, Section 5.2 |
| Max taxonomy depth | 7 levels | Chapter 5, Section 5.2 |
| Sample diversity score | ≥ 0.75 | Chapter 10, Section 10.3 |
| Coverage completeness | ≥ 0.90 | Chapter 10, Section 10.4 |
| Validation pass rate | ≥ 0.95 | Chapter 10, Section 10.5 |

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DRIFT DETECTION COMMANDS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

```bash
# Full audit for simula domain
make audit-spec-drift-domain DOMAIN=simula

# Check schema validity
python3 docs/schema/validate.py --domain simula

# Verify implementation alignment
grep -r "taxonomy" src/training/pipeline/*.py | head -20
```

